The DP has urged the opposition leaders not to abandon the government during difficult times.He has also asked all leaders to find the place and space where they can work together. Deputy President William Ruto has urged the opposition to help the government address challenges facing it in the spirit of the 'Handshake' and not to point an accusing finger at the State at its hour of need.
Dr Ruto, who was addressing a congregation at the Friends International Centre (Quakers Church), Ngong Road in Nairobi, during a requiem mass for Mama Hannah Atsianzale, mother of ANC party leader Musalia Mudavadi, said the country has serious challenges that need concerted efforts to address.



