“Let it not just be that when things are good we are in the Handshake but when they are bad you are not with us. This is not the time for us versus them. We need to pull together and deal with the situations that confront our nation,” said Dr Ruto.
Jubilee failures
He asked all leaders to find the place and space where they can work together.
“The challenges we face don’t wear ethnic regalia. They are national challenges that require national thinking, approach and a national team to address,” he said.
The DP spoke against the backdrop of Mr Odinga’s attack on him for blaming the Handshake for failures of the Jubilee government.
Mr Odinga said Dr Ruto is part of the making of the mess in the country and hence should take responsibility.
Speaking in Mombasa while meeting Muslim professionals and scholars on Sunday, the ODM leader said the BBI process will provide solutions to many national problems
“Raila hajaingia katika serikali… ako nje ya serikali… ile ambayo tumefanya mpaka leo ni kujaribu kutekeleza yale tulikubaliana na Uhuru,” said the former Prime Minister.
“Lakini yule ambaye amekuwa naibu wake kwa miaka nane anaanza kuruka… anasema yeye si responsible... analaumu mambo ya BBI… na anakula mshahara, ako na security… alafu anaanza kudhulumu hiyo serikali anasema Raila ndio ako responsible.”



