But the DP on Thursday said it was not fair for leaders in the opposition to purport to be part of the government when things are rosy for them and only run away from it during challenges.
The requiem mass was attended by National Assembly Speaker Justin Muturi, President Kenyatta’s brother Muhoho Kenyatta, Cabinet Secretary Eugene Wamalwa, who read the President’s condolence message, and a host of Senators and MPs. Opposition chief criticises Deputy President William Ruto for opposing the BBI. DP's allies say proposed referendum to change Constitution will flop nationally because it is unpopular. All funds will be channelled directly through implementing partners. Deliberations of the secret night meeting resulted in the explosive letter that has ignited the current raging fire. International broadcaster changes edits and removes some quotes.